# Hierarchical clustering to data using using Euclidean distance

#Dissimilarity matrix
d <- dist(df, method = "euclidean")

# Hierarchical clustering using Complete Linkage
hc_complete <- hclust(d, method = "complete" )

# Plot the obtained dendrogram
plot(hc_complete, cex = 0.6, hang = -1)

# Compute with agnes and with different linkage methods

m <- c( "average", "single", "complete", "ward")
names(m) <- c( "average", "single", "complete", "ward")

# function to compute coefficient
ac <- function(x) {
  agnes(df, method = x)$ac
}

map_dbl(m, ac)
##   average    single  complete      ward 
## 0.7766075 0.6067859 0.8353712 0.9046042

Using Wards method we are getting the highest agglomerative coefficient. Ward method is the best linkage method with agglomerative coefficient 0.9046042.

#Visualizing the dendogram using ward's method

cluster1 <- agnes(df, method = "ward")
pltree(cluster1, cex = 0.6, hang = -1, main = "Dendrogram of agnes")

#For identifying clusters we can cut the dendrogram with cutree()
#Create the distance matrix

d <- dist(df, method = "euclidean")

# Hierarchical clustering using Ward Linkage
cluster2 <- hclust(d, method = "ward.D2" )

# Plot the obtained dendrogram
plot(cluster2, cex = 0.6, hang = -1)

sub_grp <- cutree(cluster2, k = 4)
plot(cluster2, cex = 0.6)
rect.hclust(cluster2, k = 4, border = 2:5)

fviz_cluster(list(data = df, cluster = sub_grp))

set.seed(123)
customer1<-na.omit(customer) 

#Partition of the data
C_index<-createDataPartition(customer1$calories,p=0.5,list=FALSE)
train_data<-customer1[C_index,]
test_data<-customer1[-C_index,]
train_data<-scale(train_data[,-c(1:3)])
test_data<-scale(test_data[,-c(1:3)])

# Compute with agnes and with different linkage methods
tr <- c( "average", "single", "complete", "ward")
names(tr) <- c( "average", "single", "complete", "ward")

# function to compute coefficient
bc <- function(x) {
  agnes(train_data, method = x)$ac
}

map_dbl(tr, bc)
##   average    single  complete      ward 
## 0.7358853 0.6482111 0.7717234 0.8199919
# Compute with agnes and with different linkage methods

tt <- c( "average", "single", "complete", "ward")
names(tt) <- c( "average", "single", "complete", "ward")

# function to compute coefficient
cc <- function(x) {
  agnes(test_data, method = x)$ac
}

map_dbl(tt, cc)
##   average    single  complete      ward 
## 0.7402693 0.6713887 0.8142103 0.8457967
hc_tr<- agnes(train_data,method = "ward")
hc_tt<- agnes(test_data,method = "ward")
pltree(hc_tr,cex=0.6,hang=-1,main="Dendrogram of agnes")
rect.hclust(hc_tr, k = 3, border = 2:5)

pltree(hc_tt,cex=0.6,hang=-1,main="Dendrogram of agnes")
rect.hclust(hc_tt, k = 3, border = 2:5)
